<p>______________________________________________________________________________</p>
<p>They&#8217;re out there&#8230;<br />
<iframe width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/Dzl1RkBxNsY" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe><br />
and there&#8217;s only one way to stop them!<br />
<img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2948/15372866492_f3b6fb81d9.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="IMG_0712"></p>
<p>(1:15) I go frog-giggin&#8217; with Iliana Regan of the foraging-based Chicago restaurant Elizabeth and her friends Tonya Pierce and William &#8220;Getty&#8221; Sikora, and then see how she turns foraged frogs and childhood memories into a fine dining dish. It was a long drive, so we had a lot of time to talk about foraging as a trend and a lifestyle on the way.</p>
<p><img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2942/15372866162_5f99121269.jpg" width="500" height="333" alt="IMG_3350"></p>
<p><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3900/15372866192_64943aaaf1.jpg" width="500" height="333" alt="IMG_3469"></p>
<p>You can read more about this at the Reader <a href="http://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2014/09/24/night-of-the-frogs-gigging-with-iliana-regan-of-elizabeth">here</a> and <a href="http://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2014/09/25/how-iliana-regan-cooks-up-foraged-frogs">here</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3895/15372865512_4e9b5a1455.jpg" width="500" height="342" alt="IMG_2900"></p>
<p>(24:34) Henry Adaniya (right above) was back in town for Next&#8217;s newest menu paying tribute to his restaurant, Trio, where he gave Grant Achatz his start over a decade ago. The full interview was <a href="http://www.chicagoreader.com/Bleader/archives/2014/09/08/the-guy-who-gave-us-grant-achatz">here</a> in the Reader but I selected an excerpt about hiring, and almost not hiring, a kid named Achatz.</p>
<p><img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2949/15372865252_89c50160ac.jpg" width="500" height="333" alt="IMG_2886"><br />
<em>Black truffle explosion</em></p>
<p>(30:36) So wine retailer Craig Perman wrote <a href="https://www.facebook.com/craig.perman.7/posts/10203219613708991">this</a> on Facebook. Then Shebnem Ince, who works for him, wrote <a href="http://whatwedrank.blogspot.com/2014/09/in-which-i-review-three-italian-wine.html">this</a>, and my friend John Lenart wrote <a href="http://chicagoist.com/2014/09/05/exciting_wine_lists_in_chicago.php">this</a>. What are they all talking about? Wine lists, and why we don&#8217;t have more food writers critiquing them. So I gathered all three of them at <a href="http://www.permanwine.com">Perman Wine Selections</a> to talk about all that some more.</p>
<p><img src="https://farm3.staticflickr.com/2946/15186464560_5ca0dfd85f.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="IMG_0739"><br />
<em>Shebnem Ince, Craig Perman.</em></p>
<p>(63:13) And I read a story at the last Between Bites, at Homestead, in July, called The Squeezonk of Tolerance.</p>
<p><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3875/15186997058_5d03bd36b4.jpg" alt="" /></p>
<p>Another Between Bites event is coming up at Frontier on October 20th; <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/between-bites-tickets-13135882779">here&#8217;s how to find out more and get tickets.</a></p>
<p><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3901/15373051612_c159d224d0.jpg" width="500" height="380" alt="between bites"></p>
